WEBVTT

00:08.917 --> 00:11.208
-What's this?
-It's the lyrics for the new song

00:11.291 --> 00:15.417
we're recording on Saturday.
Learn it, live it, love it.

00:15.500 --> 00:17.041
But mostly learn it.

00:17.125 --> 00:18.792
Recording on a Saturday?

00:18.875 --> 00:21.166
When was the last time
we did anything normal on a weekend?

00:21.250 --> 00:23.917
Yeah. I just want to be able to go
hang out at the mall.

00:24.500 --> 00:25.583
Exactly.

00:26.750 --> 00:28.417
Wait, I don't wanna hang out at the mall.

00:28.500 --> 00:29.500
Me neither.

00:33.458 --> 00:34.750
[chuckles]

00:34.834 --> 00:36.917
Abby, save some for the fish.

00:39.792 --> 00:43.291
"Captain Salty's Sea Salt 'N' Vinegar
Thick-cut Salt Chips.

00:43.375 --> 00:45.792
Now with extra salty sea salt."

00:46.291 --> 00:47.750
Oh, got it.

00:48.583 --> 00:50.417
Ah. Mmm.
It's all yours!

00:50.500 --> 00:51.458
Thanks.

00:51.875 --> 00:55.041
What?
I think my hair is stuck.

00:55.291 --> 00:57.208
-It's the fire alarm.
-Feels--

00:57.291 --> 00:59.250
Let me just help you out here.

00:59.333 --> 01:01.542
-[screams softly]
-[alarm goes off]

01:05.333 --> 01:06.792
False alarm!

01:07.250 --> 01:09.709
Everyone just stay calm!

01:10.000 --> 01:13.500
Fire! Fire! Go!

01:13.583 --> 01:14.834
Put me down!

01:14.917 --> 01:18.250
Save yourselves!
[shouting]

01:22.083 --> 01:24.333
-[theme music playing]
-♪ <i>Yeah! ♪</i>

01:25.041 --> 01:26.250
<i>♪ Hey! ♪</i>

01:26.875 --> 01:28.834
<i>♪ I was sitting at home ♪</i>

01:28.917 --> 01:32.208
<i>♪ Watching TV all alone ♪</i>

01:32.291 --> 01:34.500
<i>♪ So tired of routines ♪</i>

01:34.583 --> 01:37.750
<i>♪ The day goes on and on ♪</i>

01:37.834 --> 01:39.792
<i>♪ So I pick up the phone ♪</i>

01:39.875 --> 01:43.250
<i>♪ Call everyone I know ♪</i>

01:43.333 --> 01:45.125
<i>♪ I say there's gonna be a party ♪</i>

01:45.208 --> 01:49.000
<i>♪ Hit the music, here we go, yeah ♪</i>

01:49.083 --> 01:52.542
<i>♪ You gotta live to party</i>
<i>Bust your move ♪</i>

01:52.625 --> 01:55.250
<i>♪ Everybody's in the groove ♪</i>

01:55.333 --> 01:57.917
<i>♪ Tell the DJ to play our song ♪</i>

01:58.000 --> 02:00.625
<i>♪ Are you ready to rock and roll? ♪</i>

02:00.709 --> 02:03.375
<i>♪ Gotta live to party</i>
<i>Bust your move ♪</i>

02:03.458 --> 02:06.291
<i>♪ Everybody's in the groove ♪</i>

02:06.375 --> 02:08.875
<i>♪ Live to ♪</i>

02:08.959 --> 02:10.959
<i>♪ Party! ♪</i>

02:11.417 --> 02:13.041
[ringing]

02:16.625 --> 02:18.709
Somebody care to explain what happened?

02:18.792 --> 02:21.417
-Well, my hair got stuck in--
-I've heard enough!

02:22.959 --> 02:26.333
Detention?!
That is so not fair.

02:26.417 --> 02:28.375
You can't give her detention.
It was an accident.

02:28.458 --> 02:30.291
Besides, if it's anybody's fault,
it's mine.

02:30.375 --> 02:34.208
Oh, please, like,
I'm going to give a Jonas detention?

02:34.291 --> 02:37.000
My niece would kill me.
[chuckles]

02:37.083 --> 02:40.000
Hey, Joe, can I get a quick photo?

02:43.375 --> 02:44.500
[camera clicks]

02:47.041 --> 02:48.917
Abby, I'm so sorry.

02:49.000 --> 02:52.083
It must be nice to get away with
everything just because you're famous.

02:52.166 --> 02:54.667
We don't get away with everything.
Miss Snart's new here.

02:54.750 --> 02:56.750
Everybody else treats us like normal guys,

02:56.834 --> 02:59.500
regardless of our hotness,
coolness and modesty.

02:59.583 --> 03:01.583
-[chuckles]
-[scoffs]

03:01.667 --> 03:04.083
-Abby!
-[Abby grunts softly]

03:04.750 --> 03:05.959
Abby!

03:06.041 --> 03:08.667
Macy, you have to help me.

03:09.041 --> 03:11.500
The most horrible thing has happened!

03:13.083 --> 03:15.500
Your toenails don't match your purse?

03:15.583 --> 03:18.417
OK, that would never happen.
But, seriously, read this.

03:21.834 --> 03:23.542
Oh, so, they finally figured out

03:23.625 --> 03:26.000
that you've avoided
physical education all this time.

03:26.542 --> 03:28.917
Yeah, my guidance counselor
finally got internet

03:29.041 --> 03:31.417
and realized that "shopper's elbow"
isn't a real injury.

03:31.500 --> 03:34.792
So I have until the end of the semester
to fill the requirement.

03:34.875 --> 03:38.041
-Or it's, "Hello, summer school."
-Then just take PE.

03:38.125 --> 03:39.542
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

03:39.625 --> 03:42.125
How much time do you have
to get dressed in between classes?

03:42.208 --> 03:43.667
About five minutes.

03:43.750 --> 03:48.125
There is no way that I can
accomplish this in five minutes.

03:48.208 --> 03:52.250
Stell, I've seen you change
your entire look in the elevator

03:52.333 --> 03:55.375
between the first and second floor.
What gives?

03:59.583 --> 04:01.583
You know I'm lousy at sports.

04:01.667 --> 04:04.625
Oh... [laughs]
Yeah.

04:07.792 --> 04:11.000
Thank you. Well, I don't want
everyone else to know!

04:11.083 --> 04:12.709
It's so embarrassing.

04:12.792 --> 04:15.000
Oh, OK. Well, don't worry.
I'll help you.

04:15.083 --> 04:17.750
Just meet me after school in the gym.

04:19.542 --> 04:22.458
The big red building
right next to the football field.

04:22.542 --> 04:24.500
That's the school dance building.

04:24.583 --> 04:26.709
Also known as the gym.

04:28.417 --> 04:31.250
-I knew that.
-Of course you did.

04:33.250 --> 04:35.333
-Hey, Abby, wait up.
-[sighs]

04:35.417 --> 04:36.875
Abby, I need to talk to you.

04:36.959 --> 04:39.208
Abby, I know you probably think
you got a really bad deal on detention,

04:39.291 --> 04:41.667
but if you please just let me explain,
I'm sure you would understand.

04:41.750 --> 04:43.500
Please.
Abby.

04:43.583 --> 04:44.834
Hey, the doors are closing.

04:44.917 --> 04:47.417
Abby, the doors are...
Can you open the doors, please?

04:47.834 --> 04:50.792
Guys, I can't believe
Abby's getting detention and I'm not.

04:50.875 --> 04:53.250
I don't want her or anybody at the school

04:53.333 --> 04:55.709
thinking we're getting
special treatment for being famous.

04:55.792 --> 04:57.500
I didn't know you had a thing for Abby.

04:57.583 --> 05:00.333
I don't. I just feel really bad
about what happened.

05:00.417 --> 05:03.208
Yeah. And by "feel bad,"
you mean "have a thing for."

05:03.291 --> 05:04.709
Oh, nice.

05:05.583 --> 05:08.250
You know what I have to do?
I have to get detention, too.

05:08.333 --> 05:10.583
That'll prove to Abby that we don't
get special treatment here.

05:10.750 --> 05:13.750
All right, just as long as you don't turn
this into one of your big old productions.

05:13.834 --> 05:16.875
-Kevin, get me a blueprint of the school.
-Why would I have one of those?

05:16.959 --> 05:19.041
-How about a scale model of the school?
-You got it.

05:21.917 --> 05:24.709
-This is our current position.
-All right, I just gotta think of a way

05:24.792 --> 05:29.041
that will get me into enough trouble
to get me into detention.

05:30.208 --> 05:32.000
-I'm on it.
-[keys beeping]

05:32.083 --> 05:34.125
But won't get me kicked out of school.

05:35.917 --> 05:37.458
-Oh.
-[beeps]

05:37.875 --> 05:40.750
Hi, yes, I'd like to cancel that order
I just emailed you about.

05:40.834 --> 05:43.291
Yeah, for the 20 goats
and the wheelbarrow.

05:43.375 --> 05:45.458
It's not gonna work out this time.

05:45.542 --> 05:47.709
But I still need the ducks for Saturday.

05:47.834 --> 05:49.792
[rock music plays]

05:56.500 --> 06:01.458
Ooh, this is nice.
It's really spacious.

06:01.750 --> 06:03.959
Love the hardwood floors.

06:04.041 --> 06:08.166
Thanks again for helping me, Mace.
I mean, I know this can be a challenge.

06:08.250 --> 06:10.333
Oh, that's what best friends do,
they help each other.

06:10.417 --> 06:13.250
Like the time I broke my ankle
and you painted my toenails,

06:13.333 --> 06:15.542
so they'd look good
when the boys signed my cast.

06:15.625 --> 06:17.542
[both] Aww.

06:19.959 --> 06:21.917
OK.
So let's find out what you're good at.

06:22.000 --> 06:23.542
We're gonna start with something easy.

06:27.875 --> 06:29.667
[Stella]
Oh! [chuckles]

06:29.750 --> 06:34.208
Um... that's something easy?

06:34.291 --> 06:36.667
Sure!
Try it!

06:37.709 --> 06:38.917
Uh-huh.

06:39.375 --> 06:40.875
Stella, are you trying it?

06:40.959 --> 06:42.750
-Yep.
-Oh, isn't it fun?

06:42.834 --> 06:45.208
-Mm...
-This is, like, my favorite thing to do.

06:45.291 --> 06:47.667
You're gonna be so awesome.
[chuckles]

06:47.959 --> 06:49.375
Phew!

06:51.125 --> 06:52.083
That was fun!

06:52.166 --> 06:53.959
-Oh, please.
-What?

06:55.083 --> 06:56.750
Good afternoon, everyone.

06:56.834 --> 07:02.250
Let's start with silent reading:
chapters one through 11.

07:10.333 --> 07:14.083
[popping]

07:14.166 --> 07:17.250
-Who's doing that?
-It's me, Miss Snart. [chuckles]

07:17.333 --> 07:19.083
I'll just send myself to detention.

07:19.166 --> 07:23.458
Actually, I was gonna
send this to my grandma for her birthday.

07:23.542 --> 07:25.875
You just saved me a trip
to the post office!

07:25.959 --> 07:30.000
You may skip homework
for the next three days.

07:30.083 --> 07:32.166
[students murmuring]

07:37.750 --> 07:41.834
You know what, everyone?
Joe has made me so happy.

07:42.083 --> 07:45.417
-I'm gonna give a pop quiz!
-[students groan]

07:45.500 --> 07:49.834
That sound is the sweet nectar
that I thrive on.

07:56.583 --> 08:00.917
Hey, Kevin, what did you
get on question number three?

08:01.166 --> 08:04.083
I'd really like you to tell me
the answer to that.

08:04.166 --> 08:06.792
Eyes on your own paper!

08:07.333 --> 08:09.458
[whispers]
It's "mitosis."

08:23.458 --> 08:25.000
[beeping]

08:25.667 --> 08:28.333
[phone playing rock music]
<i>♪ Everybody, bust your move... ♪</i>

08:28.417 --> 08:30.959
Oh, that's me.
[chuckles]

08:31.041 --> 08:33.417
<i>♪ Everybody, bust your move... ♪</i>

08:33.458 --> 08:35.083
Nope.

08:35.166 --> 08:37.125
Huh. No.

08:37.917 --> 08:40.333
Hello?
[chuckles]

08:40.417 --> 08:43.834
[groans]
How are you guys doing?

08:43.917 --> 08:45.834
<i>♪ Everybody... ♪</i>

08:45.917 --> 08:49.500
Hello. You've got Joe.
No, this is a perfectly good time.

08:49.583 --> 08:51.083
I'm just hanging out at school.
[chuckles]

08:51.166 --> 08:53.417
-Excuse me!
-Yes, Miss Snart?

08:53.500 --> 08:55.792
Is that the new Jonas ringtone?

08:55.875 --> 08:57.000
Can you beam it to my phone?

08:58.917 --> 08:59.875
Sure.

09:01.125 --> 09:02.542
[groans]

09:05.792 --> 09:08.625
It's just, like, whatever I try,
I just can't get detention.

09:08.709 --> 09:10.917
Just give me the word, man.
I can have 20 goats here by lunch.

09:11.000 --> 09:12.083
No, thank you.

09:14.000 --> 09:15.750
Hello, Vice Principal Smetzer.

09:15.834 --> 09:18.291
Don't try to charm me, mister.

09:18.375 --> 09:21.959
I'm not impressed by your
rock and roll dimples.

09:23.417 --> 09:28.166
Willful disobedience of school signage.
Detention!

09:29.375 --> 09:32.667
-Oh, no.
-Oh, yes.

09:46.583 --> 09:49.709
OK, well, that rules out anything
that requires a racket...

09:50.083 --> 09:55.166
any kind of ball, an opponent,
a scoring system or movement of limbs.

09:55.667 --> 10:00.000
[groans] There has got to be
something that I can do.

10:00.917 --> 10:05.625
Ooh, what about "bow and arrows?"

10:05.792 --> 10:07.542
If you mean archery,

10:07.625 --> 10:09.083
that requires strength,
and discipline and precision.

10:09.166 --> 10:12.291
And even if you had
strength and discipline,

10:12.375 --> 10:14.250
you'd still need precision.

10:14.583 --> 10:16.750
How hard can this be?

10:22.291 --> 10:26.875
-Well, that was very good for a beginner!
-Oh, please.

10:26.959 --> 10:28.250
[Kevin] OK, a little higher on the left.

10:28.333 --> 10:30.291
A little lower on the left.

10:30.375 --> 10:32.625
Up a little bit on the left.
A little down on the left.

10:32.709 --> 10:34.959
A little up on the left.
Almost there. Almost there!

10:35.041 --> 10:37.083
No. Down on the left.
Nick, is this my left

10:37.166 --> 10:39.917
-or your left you're looking at?
-It's the same left!

10:40.000 --> 10:42.542
Yes! I got detention tomorrow!

10:42.625 --> 10:44.709
Now Abby will see
I get punished like everybody else.

10:44.792 --> 10:47.083
Plus, once she's in there,
she'll be a captive audience.

10:47.166 --> 10:49.375
-She'll have to listen to me. Ha!
-Whoa, whoa, whoa.

10:49.458 --> 10:51.917
-What do you mean tomorrow?
-[Kevin] You know, the day after today

10:52.000 --> 10:54.709
-or the day before two days from now.
-Also known as the same day

10:54.792 --> 10:56.250
we have to record the vocals
for the new record

10:56.333 --> 10:59.333
-or we miss the deadline.
-Oh, I forgot about that.

10:59.417 --> 11:01.291
-Nick, a little up on the right.
-Would somebody please

11:01.375 --> 11:03.250
get me something to hang this with?

11:04.959 --> 11:06.542
Thanks.

11:10.375 --> 11:11.500
How'd I do?

11:17.875 --> 11:19.083
Hi.

11:20.458 --> 11:23.625
-I got detention for you.
-Yeah, I remember.

11:23.709 --> 11:26.792
That's why all my friends
are at the mall and I'm not.

11:26.875 --> 11:31.500
I meant I got myself detention
because I accidentally got you detention.

11:31.917 --> 11:33.959
I just wanted a chance to explain things.

11:36.166 --> 11:40.500
All right. My brothers and I
are regular guys with regular dreams.

11:41.125 --> 11:42.333
Hold on a second.

11:45.208 --> 11:47.083
Can you take it from the bridge?

11:50.500 --> 11:51.417
[dramatic song playing]

11:51.500 --> 11:53.500
You see, we come from
a small town in New Jersey.

11:53.583 --> 11:55.125
-[door opens]
-We didn't grow up with much,

11:55.208 --> 11:56.625
just love and fresh air.

11:56.709 --> 12:00.083
-[door slams]
-Welcome to detention.

12:03.500 --> 12:05.125
[fast music playing]

12:05.208 --> 12:07.875
I see you're getting
to know one another...

12:08.625 --> 12:10.875
[chuckles]
Which is odd because...

12:10.959 --> 12:13.625
[shouts]
There's no talking in detention!

12:13.709 --> 12:16.667
Luckily, I do have a solution.

12:17.500 --> 12:20.875
-No... But...
-[Smetzer] No arguing.

12:20.959 --> 12:23.250
-Also, no texting. No note passing.
-[beeping]

12:23.333 --> 12:25.667
And no morse code, Gary!

12:29.583 --> 12:34.875
I want complete
and utter silence in this room.

12:34.959 --> 12:37.667
-Am I understood?
-Yes, sir.

12:37.750 --> 12:39.458
That was a trick question!

12:39.542 --> 12:41.125
[shouts]
I said silence!

12:42.875 --> 12:46.375
I am going to be in my office.

12:47.000 --> 12:50.417
But don't try any malarkey.

12:50.500 --> 12:54.709
One peep and you'll spend
the next four weekends

12:54.792 --> 12:58.458
helping the school janitors
scoop squirrels out of the pool filter.

13:00.542 --> 13:01.792
That's right.

13:01.875 --> 13:08.500
I'm quick and I'm quiet,
so don't try any malarkey.

13:11.709 --> 13:14.792
I'm like a detention ninja.

13:14.875 --> 13:18.250
I could show up anywhere.

13:23.250 --> 13:25.250
-[gasps]
-Oh, yeah.

13:39.750 --> 13:41.000
OK.

13:41.083 --> 13:44.458
And surprisingly, no to hop scotch.

13:44.542 --> 13:47.750
OK.
How am I supposed to bend down

13:47.834 --> 13:50.792
and pick something up
while I'm standing on one foot?

13:50.875 --> 13:53.834
I mean, what am I, a spider monkey?

13:53.917 --> 13:57.750
That's every sport recognized
by this school district.

13:57.834 --> 14:00.500
No, no, no, no, no, no.
No, Macy, that can't be!

14:00.583 --> 14:03.250
If I don't pass PE, I'm gonna
have to make this up in summer school.

14:03.333 --> 14:07.417
I mean, there has to be some sport
that I can get credit for!

14:08.417 --> 14:10.250
Like, what about...

14:10.333 --> 14:14.083
What about this?
Isn't this a sport?

14:14.166 --> 14:16.166
No, that's clapping your hands
over your head.

14:17.500 --> 14:19.125
What about this?

14:20.000 --> 14:22.125
I'm not sure what that is,
but you're scaring me.

14:23.417 --> 14:25.208
-You know what I can do?
-Huh?

14:25.291 --> 14:26.667
I can do this!

14:28.041 --> 14:31.125
No, you can't.
It's like this.

14:37.500 --> 14:38.834
I can't even sit.

14:43.792 --> 14:45.625
[gasps]
Where'd you guys come from?

14:45.709 --> 14:47.709
A small town in New Jersey.

14:47.834 --> 14:50.917
-What's up, troublemakers?
-[students] Shh!

14:51.000 --> 14:53.542
-What are you guys doing here?
-We have to record the new vocals.

14:53.625 --> 14:56.250
The record label needs it
by the end of the day today.

14:56.333 --> 14:59.542
If Mr. Smetzer hears me,
I'm getting suspended.

14:59.625 --> 15:02.834
-That's a chance I'm willing to take.
-Me too.

15:02.917 --> 15:06.000
Oh, thanks a lot, guys.
Fine, I'll do it, OK?

15:06.083 --> 15:09.417
-Just gotta talk to Abby first.
-Your apologies take forever.

15:09.500 --> 15:12.291
-We'll talk to her for you.
-Wait. Guys...

15:12.458 --> 15:15.166
Hi, Nick. Kevin.
Look, Joe feels really bad

15:15.250 --> 15:17.417
about getting you into trouble.
He wants to apologize.

15:17.500 --> 15:19.667
Oh, so he sent over two spokesmodels?

15:21.458 --> 15:23.250
Wow, must be really nice

15:23.333 --> 15:25.458
not to have to do
any dirty work yourself.

15:26.583 --> 15:29.291
Oh, look, the chapter's about forgiveness.

15:32.000 --> 15:37.208
I don't get it.
Why do you wanna go out with... her?

15:37.291 --> 15:38.625
I don't wanna go out with her!

15:38.709 --> 15:41.375
Did I hear talking?!

15:43.250 --> 15:45.083
Hmm.

15:45.250 --> 15:49.125
Something's not right here.

15:52.500 --> 15:54.500
Hmm...

16:00.458 --> 16:01.625
Ah-ha!

16:02.583 --> 16:04.917
[laughs]

16:05.000 --> 16:06.625
Yes.

16:11.000 --> 16:13.709
There we are.

16:14.083 --> 16:15.291
[rock music playing]

16:20.709 --> 16:22.792
Stella, I'm sorry.
I feel like I let you down.

16:22.875 --> 16:24.792
No, no, no, no.
You did everything you could.

16:24.875 --> 16:26.834
You're amazing.
It's not you, it's me.

16:26.917 --> 16:30.083
-I'm a failure.
-Stella, you are not a failure.

16:30.166 --> 16:32.208
Sports just aren't your thing.

16:33.417 --> 16:36.291
Yeah?
All right. I've gotta go.

16:36.375 --> 16:40.041
I've got volleyball practice,
and we haven't won a game all season.

16:40.333 --> 16:42.709
Well, it's no wonder.
I mean, look at your uniforms.

16:42.792 --> 16:44.875
The shorts are bulky,
the top is too tight.

16:44.959 --> 16:47.291
I know. Every time I wear this,
I sweat like a pig.

16:48.041 --> 16:50.083
I'm mean, I glisten like a pig.

16:50.166 --> 16:52.709
Well, yeah. That's because that kind
of fabric doesn't breathe.

16:52.792 --> 16:55.250
Not to mention the frumpy factor.

16:55.333 --> 16:57.291
I mean, if you don't look good,

16:57.375 --> 16:59.917
-You're not going to play good.
-I play good.

17:00.083 --> 17:02.000
But do you look good?

17:04.750 --> 17:06.125
Hmm.

17:10.750 --> 17:11.834
Hey, Abby.

17:12.166 --> 17:14.208
Abby? Abby, I'm sorry.

17:14.959 --> 17:16.875
I'm sorry you think I get
special treatment around here

17:16.959 --> 17:19.000
-because I really don't.
-[scoffs]

17:19.083 --> 17:20.542
I mean, the only person
in the whole school

17:20.625 --> 17:22.542
who gives me special treatment
is Miss Snart.

17:23.208 --> 17:27.041
If it's anybody but her,
I get punished like everyone else.

17:27.125 --> 17:30.333
Hello. I'm filling in
for Vice Principal Smetzer

17:30.417 --> 17:32.667
who had to go home
for a family emergency.

17:32.750 --> 17:36.083
His mother's bath was overflowing.

17:36.166 --> 17:38.667
Joe! What are you doing in here?

17:38.750 --> 17:42.625
And the two remaining two-thirds of Jonas!

17:42.709 --> 17:46.875
Did you prank up some mischief,
you little rascals?

17:48.125 --> 17:49.583
[sighs]

17:51.417 --> 17:53.792
Stella, I have great news!

17:53.875 --> 17:56.709
I talked to my volleyball coach
about our frumpy uniforms

17:56.792 --> 17:57.875
that are making us lose.

17:57.959 --> 18:02.667
And she said if you can design
12 new uniforms by game-time tomorrow,

18:02.750 --> 18:05.959
she can give you full PE credit.

18:06.041 --> 18:09.250
Macy... I love you!

18:09.375 --> 18:10.291
[squealing]

18:10.375 --> 18:12.417
-Thank you! Thank you.
-You're welcome.

18:13.041 --> 18:14.041
So can you do it?

18:14.125 --> 18:16.041
Just watch me.

18:16.125 --> 18:17.959
But first...

18:18.834 --> 18:22.792
-I need some dynamic music.
-[rock music playing]

18:22.875 --> 18:25.166
<i>♪ Oh, yeah! ♪</i>

18:34.041 --> 18:37.291
<i>♪ Living life, life in the fast lane</i>

18:37.375 --> 18:40.208
<i>♪ Not that bad, no, we can't complain ♪</i>

18:40.291 --> 18:43.959
<i>♪ Who's to say</i>
<i>That we won't keep it real? ♪</i>

18:44.041 --> 18:45.417
<i>♪ Yeah! ♪</i>

18:45.500 --> 18:48.041
<i>♪ Hold on tight</i>
<i>Don't you dare let go ♪</i>

18:48.125 --> 18:51.041
<i>♪ Now's the time</i>
<i>Let the whole world know ♪</i>

18:51.125 --> 18:55.667
<i>♪ You can shine bright</i>
<i>But still keep it real ♪</i>

19:01.000 --> 19:04.000
Stella, this is amazing.

19:04.083 --> 19:07.000
Look how free I am,
yet, as cute as a button.

19:08.041 --> 19:10.375
[sighs]
Whoever says you aren't an athlete

19:10.458 --> 19:13.500
hasn't seen you with a pair of scissors
and measuring tape.

19:15.000 --> 19:16.417
Thanks, Macy.

19:16.875 --> 19:19.083
Coming from you,
that really means a lot to me.

19:19.166 --> 19:20.750
[both] Aww.

19:23.625 --> 19:24.959
[Macy sighs]

19:26.333 --> 19:30.125
So one down, 11 more to go, right?

19:31.458 --> 19:32.333
Oh, yeah.

19:32.375 --> 19:35.417
<i>♪ Oh, yeah! ♪</i>

19:37.417 --> 19:40.166
Now before taking over for Mr. Smetzer,

19:40.291 --> 19:43.667
I was helping out at the varsity girls'
swim team victory party.

19:43.750 --> 19:47.875
So I need someone
to go pass out pizza and towels.

19:47.959 --> 19:49.208
Any volunteers?

19:50.166 --> 19:53.583
Mm, eenie-meenie-miney...

19:53.667 --> 19:56.000
Joe!
Have fun!

19:56.083 --> 19:57.959
You know what,
I think I should probably stay here.

19:58.041 --> 20:00.917
I mean, I walked on grass.
I should think about what I've done.

20:01.000 --> 20:05.000
Are you disobeying
a direct order from a teacher?

20:06.750 --> 20:08.875
Yes, I am.

20:08.959 --> 20:11.083
And I think you should
give me more detention.

20:11.166 --> 20:12.583
[Abby] Wait.

20:12.750 --> 20:15.417
You really don't expect
special treatment?

20:15.500 --> 20:18.208
No, Abby, that's what
I've been trying to tell you.

20:19.250 --> 20:20.542
Cool.

20:21.709 --> 20:23.125
I'm impressed.

20:26.500 --> 20:29.000
Do I have another volunteer?

20:29.083 --> 20:30.166
I'll do it!

20:31.000 --> 20:35.083
Have fun. And when the party's over,
grab a gift bag and just go on home.

20:36.750 --> 20:38.959
-Abby, but--
-See ya!

20:42.000 --> 20:44.375
That girl is just no good.

20:44.875 --> 20:46.917
I know Joe doesn't want
any special treatment,

20:47.000 --> 20:48.917
but we kind of have a new song
to finish recording.

20:49.000 --> 20:50.583
Do you mind if we do it in here?

20:50.667 --> 20:52.709
Do I mind?

20:53.667 --> 20:56.083
This is a detention room, young man.

20:56.166 --> 20:59.083
I can't believe you even asked me that.

20:59.166 --> 21:00.625
Sorry.

21:00.709 --> 21:04.250
The acoustics are way better in the hall!

21:04.333 --> 21:05.959
You rapscallion.

21:07.583 --> 21:11.417
-[rock music plays]
<i>♪ I try to turn on my TV ♪</i>

21:11.500 --> 21:14.500
<i>♪ To get you out of my head ♪</i>

21:15.458 --> 21:18.375
<i>♪ Feeling something deep inside ♪</i>

21:18.458 --> 21:20.917
<i>♪ That I just won't admit ♪</i>

21:21.000 --> 21:24.709
<i>♪ It's not like I don't ♪</i>

21:24.792 --> 21:28.500
<i>-♪ Wanna commit ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Wanna commit ♪</i>

21:28.583 --> 21:31.000
<i>♪ I just don't know why ♪</i>

21:31.083 --> 21:34.875
<i>♪ I can't stop feeling like this ♪</i>

21:34.959 --> 21:38.542
<i>-♪ Tell me why ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Why, why? ♪</i>

21:38.625 --> 21:42.000
<i>♪ Does it hurt so bad? ♪</i>

21:42.083 --> 21:45.458
<i>-♪ Tell me why ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Why, why? ♪</i>

21:45.542 --> 21:49.041
<i>♪ Does it make me mad? ♪</i>

21:49.125 --> 21:52.083
<i>♪ Tell me why ♪</i>

21:56.083 --> 21:58.250
<i>♪ Tell me why ♪</i>

22:04.083 --> 22:07.166
<i>♪ Now I can see the storm's ♪</i>

22:07.250 --> 22:09.000
<i>♪ Not gonna clear ♪</i>

22:09.083 --> 22:10.792
<i>♪ Not gonna clear ♪</i>

22:10.875 --> 22:14.417
<i>♪ Drenched in my pain ♪</i>

22:14.500 --> 22:16.959
<i>♪ And all of my tears ♪</i>

22:17.041 --> 22:20.417
<i>-♪ Tell me why ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Why, why? ♪</i>

22:20.500 --> 22:23.667
<i>♪ Does it hurt so bad? ♪</i>

22:23.750 --> 22:25.917
<i>-♪ You make it hurt so bad ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Tell me why ♪</i>

22:26.000 --> 22:31.792
<i>-♪ Why, why? ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Does it make me mad? ♪</i>

22:31.875 --> 22:34.875
[all cheering]

22:37.542 --> 22:40.542
[classical music playing]

22:43.625 --> 22:46.000
Now this is how
we should spend a Saturday.

22:46.083 --> 22:49.667
No recordings, no detention.

22:50.000 --> 22:51.667
Nick, can you move
a little bit to the left?

22:52.834 --> 22:53.834
Perfect.

22:57.125 --> 22:58.458
Yes!

22:58.750 --> 23:01.166
Hey, Nick, keep an eye on me.
I think I'm cheating.

23:02.250 --> 23:05.667
<i>Voilà!</i>
My masterpiece, she is finished!

23:05.959 --> 23:07.917
Whoa.
Very realistic, Kevin.

23:08.041 --> 23:09.417
<i>Merci.</i>

23:11.750 --> 23:15.000
So I sat and held that book
all day for this?

23:15.083 --> 23:17.250
-I'm not even in it.
-Yes, you are.

23:17.333 --> 23:20.542
-That's my finger!
-You recognized it!

23:20.834 --> 23:22.333
I'm better than I thought.
